# Headless Machine (Automation Only, No Interactive Sessions)
#
# This machine runs scheduled jobs but no human ever opens an
# interactive Claude Code session here. The PreToolUse "Read" hook
# never fires, so the auto-pull mechanism from settings.json doesn't
# work on this machine. You need a scheduled pull instead.
#
# See the "Headless Machines" section in README.md for the full
# rationale. Customize repo names and commit prefix for your setup.

## Shared Memory

This machine has access to the following memory repos:
- **shared-identity**: ~/repos/shared-identity/ (read-write)
- **automation-memory**: ~/repos/automation-memory/ (read-write, source of truth for this machine's domain)

### Scheduled pull (required)
Because no interactive session ever runs here, the auto-pull hook
from settings.json never fires. Instead, piggyback
`git pull --ff-only` onto an existing scheduled job (cron, launchd,
systemd timer). Prefer piggybacking over a dedicated sync-only job
— fewer moving parts, and the pull runs exactly when fresh data
matters most (right before the job reads memory).

See `templates/headless-sync.sh` for a drop-in example.

### When to check shared repos
If the user asks about a specific project, tool, repo, system, or name that you don't immediately recognize — check the MEMORY.md index in each shared repo before saying "I don't know." If any index references the topic, read the linked file before responding.
Do NOT do this for general knowledge questions. Only check repos when the question is about something specific to the user's projects or infrastructure.

### Rules
- Domain-specific memories → automation-memory
- Universal memories (user prefs, collaboration style, feedback that applies everywhere) → shared-identity
- After writing to a shared repo:
  ```bash
  cd ~/repos/<repo> && git add -A && git commit -m "[headless] description" && git push
  ```
- If the scheduled pull hasn't run yet this session, the local clone may be stale. Prefer `git pull --ff-only` before reading if timing matters.
